ă deflate.a+ ßßß DEFLATE Decompressor (RFC 1951) ßßß
ă
ă RFC 1951 DEFLATE decompressor supporting fixed Huffman (BTYPE=01).
ă Reads bitstream from byte array, LSB-first within bytes.
ă Huffman codes are packed MSB-first per the RFC.
ă Decodes literal bytes and LZ77 length/distance back-references.
ă
ă === Bit Reader ===  data=byte array,  bp=bit position (0-based) ===
ă Read 1 bit from data at global bit position bp. Returns 0 or 1.
br_read_bit{data;bp}: {
  byte_idxűbpß8
  bit_idxűbp - byte_idx*8
  byte_valűdata[byte_idx]
  (byte_valß(1Ábit_idx)) & 1
}

ă Read n bits (1-15) from data at position bp. Returns integer value.
br_read_bits{data;bp;n}: {
  valű0
  iű0
  while (i<n) {
    bitűbr_read_bit{data;bp+i}
    if (bit) { valűval + (1Ái) }
    iűi+1
  }
  val
}

ă === Fixed Huffman Decode Table ===
ă Literal/length: 512 entries for 9-bit max code length.
ă Each entry: [code_length, symbol_value] stored in fht_len, fht_sym.
ă Table indexed by bitstream-read value (LSB-read of MSB-packed code).
fht_symű512Î0
fht_lenű512Î0

ă Build the table: for each symbol 0-287, compute its canonical code,
ă reverse it (since we read LSB-first but codes are MSB-packed),
ă and fill all suffix combinations for 9-bit lookup.
iű0
while (i<288) {
  ă Determine code and length for symbol i
  if (i<=143) {
    codeű0x30 + i
    cbitsű8
  }
  if ((i>=144) & (i<=255)) {
    codeű0x190 + (i-144)
    cbitsű9
  }
  if ((i>=256) & (i<=279)) {
    codeűi-256
    cbitsű7
  }
  if (i>=280) {
    codeű0xC0 + (i-280)
    cbitsű8
  }
  ă Reverse bits (code stored MSB, but we read LSB first)
  revű0
  jű0
  while (j<cbits) {
    if (code & (1Áj)) { revűrev + (1Á(cbits-1-j)) }
    jűj+1
  }
  ă Fill all suffix combinations for 9-bit index
  sfx_bitsű9 - cbits
  sfx_maxű1
  kű0
  while (k<sfx_bits) { sfx_maxűsfx_max * 2; kűk+1 }
  sfx_maxűsfx_max - 1
  sű0
  while (s<=sfx_max) {
    idxűrev + (sÁcbits)
    fht_len[idx]űcbits
    fht_sym[idx]űi
    sűs+1
  }
  iűi+1
}

ă Distance decode table: 32 entries (5-bit codes, all same length)
fhd_symű32Î0
fhd_lenű32Î0
iű0
while (i<30) {
  fhd_sym[i]űi
  fhd_len[i]ű5
  iűi+1
}

